<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-10-06T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-10-06T16:00:00-05:00" n="220" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d220">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">611.3531/523: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Weddell</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos
                                        Aires</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-10-06T17:00:00-04:00">October 6, 1937—5
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received October 6—4:17 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>190. Department’s telegram No. 92, October 5, 2 p.m. I delivered the
                            confidential memorandum to the Minister for Foreign Affairs today and
                            expect to discuss it with him tomorrow.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Weddell</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>